The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Sonia plea for peace
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Sonia plea for peace
                            
	New Delhi, July 26 (PTI): Leaders from various political parties, including Congress president Sonia Gandhi, today expressed deep shock at the Ahmedabad serial blasts and condemned them as an act of desperation and cowardice aimed at disturbing peace and harmony in the country.        
	While condoling the death of innocent citizens, Sonia appealed to the people to maintain peace.        
	A Congress delegation will visit Ahmedabad tomorrow for an on-the-spot study of the situation.         
	Leader of the Opposition L.K. Advani said the loopholes in the anti-terrorist framework have been exposed by this incident.                                                                                                                                                                          
